## ğŸ”§ How OOP Concepts Connect to Database

### 1. **Inheritance Mapping**
```
Person (users table)
  â†“
Passenger (users + passengers tables)
Pilot (users + employees + pilots tables)
CrewMember (users + employees + crew_members tables)
```

### 2. **Validation Flow**
1. User enters data in GUI
2. Data passed to OOP class constructor
3. Setters validate data (throw IllegalArgumentException)
4. If valid, data saved to database
5. If invalid, error shown in GUI

### 3. **Bounded Generics in Action**
```java
// In PassengerDashboard
Booking<Passenger> booking = new Booking<>(
    passenger,  // Must be Person or subclass
    flight,
    price,
    seat
);
```

### 4. **Polymorphism in Login**
```java
// Same login code handles all roles
switch (role) {
    case "ADMIN":
        new AdminDashboard(userId, name).open();
        break;
    case "PILOT":
    case "CREW":
        new EmployeeDashboard(userId, name, role).open();
        break;
    case "PASSENGER":
        new PassengerDashboard(userId, name).open();
        break;
}
```

